review_text: I use this all year round here in the south. Fire Ants are a part of life here, and this product works wonders at keeping the painful little #@%*s out of my lawn! If you discover a new mound sprinkle this around the outer edges, as per directions, and walk away. Do not apply water like you would with other products. The fire Ant foraging crew will find this, collect it, and bring it back to the colony. Once there it gets placed into the colonies food storage and starts being consumed in short order. Depending on the size of the mound it can take several days to work its majic, so be patient. Ive seen mounds die within as little as a 24 hours if theyre new, and as long as a week if its a really big established colony. Again, be patient. This product will provide a very thorough kill. **Read the cautions on the label regarding application and amount to use.** This shouldnt be used if pets can access the treated area directly after application. In the warmer months I personally treat in early evening because, in my experience, most of the bait has been collected by the colony before the next morning. Unlike some of the other treatments available, this product doesnt have a strong toxic smell, but it works!

product_name: Pennington Planter Hummingbird Feeder (2 pack)
review_text: Our report is from SEPA (South East Pennsylvania). These single port feeders are the best !!! Little waste, and easy clean-up. They come with pre-bent hangers with a bent hook on one end while the opposing end of the hanger is straight - useless hook ! We bend the straight end into a hook and hang the feeder from a screw - viola - our feeders are away from the ground.We use eight (8) of these feeders on our property for two reasons. First, hummingbirds are hugely territorial. They expend lots of extra energy defending larger multi-port feeders. One port on these feeders keeps down the defensive combat to "just a few times a day" rather than "all day long." We think this helps the birds conserve energy. And second, with 6 active feeders hidden from each other on separate sides of our house we can support different troops of hummers on our property.In "heavy use locations " hummers can drain one of these feeders in 4-5 days. Under "normal use" these feeders will last past 7 days. We clean and change our feeders ever 5-7 days depending on traffic and the season.

review_title: Easy to clean, hummingbirds love it
review_text: I did a lot of research on which feeders were the best for staying clean, avoiding rust, and keeping the birds happy, and all the feeders I looked into had some complaint or another. My top priority was bird health - I wanted something that I could get absolutely clean with no fuss, and of course I wanted something the birds would actually like. This feeder checked those boxes. It is easy to take completely apart and Ive run it through the dishwasher twice so far, no problems. There are zero metal parts, except for the hanging section, so no risk of rust. I also have more birds than ever. I once saw three birds feeding at once, and out here on the West coast with the Annas hummingbirds thats quite unusual, theyre very territorial. If youre struggling with which feeder to buy, and you dont care about the look of the feeder, just want something good for the birds, go with this one.
